The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, June 23, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, June 23, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Lower Circular Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, due to the final phase of work on the AJC Bose Road flyover. Buses and minibuses heading from Beckbagan to Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-Lower Circular Road route. Those travelling east to Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route.				 																Hard Talk				 																																	Mayor of Calcutta Municipal Corporation Subrata Mukherjee will meet readers of The Telegraph at the Corporation conference hall, 7 pm.				 																Discussion				 																																	Sexplicity, a panel discussion on modern-day sexual mores, at Oxford Bookstore from 7 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	An exhibition of prints and posters of the European and Indian masters at Vikalp Art Shop, Swabhumi, from 4 pm to 8 pm.				 																																	Summer Show of Affordable Heritage, an exhibition of paintings of the last century at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, from 4 pm to 8 pm.
